---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import Nav from '../../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Acknowledgments — Aplica DS"
  description="The people and projects that made the Aplica Tokens Theme Engine possible."
>
  <Nav lang="en" />

  <section style="padding: 5rem 0;">
    <div class="container" style="max-width: 720px;">

      <p style="font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.8125rem; color: var(--color-accent); font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 1rem; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em;">Acknowledgments</p>

      <h1 style="font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 4vw, 2.5rem); font-weight: 700; line-height: 1.2; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
        Standing on the shoulders of giants
      </h1>

      <p style="font-size: 1.0625rem; color: var(--color-text-muted); line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 1rem; font-style: italic;">
        "If I have seen further, it is by standing on the shoulders of Giants." — Isaac Newton
      </p>

      <p style="font-size: 1rem; color: var(--color-text-muted); line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 3rem;">
        Aplica Tokens Theme Engine is a synthesis. It wouldn't exist without the work, ideas, and generosity of the people and projects below.
      </p>

      <hr style="border: none; border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border); margin-bottom: 3rem;" />

      <!-- Community -->
      <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 2.5rem; margin-bottom: 3.5rem;">

        <div>
          <h2 style="font-size: 1.125rem; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">Tokens Studio · Hyma</h2>
          <p style="color: var(--color-text-muted); font-size: 0.9375rem; line-height: 1.75;">
            I've been using Tokens Studio since 2020. <strong>Jan Six</strong>'s brilliant idea and the work of everyone who championed the plugin through <strong>Hyma</strong> opened the bridge between design tokens and Figma in a way that changed how the entire field works.
          </p>
          <a href="https://tokens.studio" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="display: inline-block; margin-top: 0.5rem; font-size: 0.875rem; color: var(--color-accent); text-decoration: none;">tokens.studio ↗</a>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 style="font-size: 1.125rem; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">W3C Design Tokens Community Group</h2>
          <p style="color: var(--color-text-muted); font-size: 0.9375rem; line-height: 1.75;">
            The structures the group is formalizing gave rigor to what was previously convention. A shared language the entire ecosystem needed.
          </p>
          <a href="https://design-tokens.github.io/community-group" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="display: inline-block; margin-top: 0.5rem; font-size: 0.875rem; color: var(--color-accent); text-decoration: none;">design-tokens.github.io ↗</a>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 style="font-size: 1.125rem; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">Brad Frost</h2>
          <p style="color: var(--color-text-muted); font-size: 0.9375rem; line-height: 1.75;">
            Since 2013, his insights taught the community to think in systems before thinking in components. Those ideas never stopped echoing.
          </p>
          <a href="https://bradfrost.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="display: inline-block; margin-top: 0.5rem; font-size: 0.875rem; color: var(--color-accent); text-decoration: none;">bradfrost.com ↗</a>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 style="font-size: 1.125rem; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">Nathan Curtis</h2>
          <p style="color: var(--color-text-muted); font-size: 0.9375rem; line-height: 1.75;">
            He articulated with precision what few dared to say: that handoff is far more than a visual artifact — it's the integration between design intent and product construction. An idea that changed how entire teams think about collaboration in systems.
          </p>
        </div>

      </div>

      <hr style="border: none; border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border); margin-bottom: 3rem;" />

      <!-- Close collaborators -->
      <div>
        <h2 style="font-size: 1.125rem; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">Close collaborators</h2>

        <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 2rem;">

          <div>
            <p style="font-weight: 600; font-size: 0.9375rem; margin-bottom: 0.375rem;">Rafael Sanches · Gabriel Esnacke</p>
            <p style="color: var(--color-text-muted); font-size: 0.9375rem; line-height: 1.75;">
              Throughout our time working together, they understood and supported the technical evolution of Aplica in a way few would. The clarity of those who see the system from the inside makes all the difference.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <p style="font-weight: 600; font-size: 0.9375rem; margin-bottom: 0.375rem;">Lucas Figueiredo</p>
            <p style="color: var(--color-text-muted); font-size: 0.9375rem; line-height: 1.75;">
              He dove into this madness as someone genuinely critical and engaged. Two years of injecting energy and raising always-surgical questions — making me think sharper with every conversation.
            </p>
          </div>

        </div>
      </div>

      <hr style="border: none; border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border); margin-top: 3.5rem; margin-bottom: 2rem;" />

      <p style="color: var(--color-text-muted); font-size: 0.875rem; line-height: 1.7;">
        Aplica Tokens Theme Engine is open source under the Apache-2.0 license.<br />
        See also: <a href="/humans.txt" style="color: var(--color-accent); text-decoration: none;">humans.txt</a>
      </p>

    </div>
  </section>

  <Footer lang="en" />
</Base>
